-- COMPUTATIONAL_EVIDENCE gap4-5040-sat:
--   description:
--     ILP feasibility analysis for 31-prime set on 5040^2 torus, plus simulated
--     annealing (SA) and exhaustive moduli survey. Extends sat-5040-result with
--     formal ILP attempts and maximality certificate for the 31-prime set.
--   ilp_formulation:
--     Binary variables: y_{p,r} = 1 iff prime p uses residue r; 9279 binary variables
--       (one per (prime, residue) pair, summed over all 31 primes and their |H_p| residues).
--     Constraints: for each of the 7000 seed uncovered cells (k,l), at least one
--       prime-residue variable covering that cell must be set to 1.
--     Solver: CBC 2.10.3 (branch-and-bound ILP solver via PuLP 2.8.0).
--   ilp_results:
--     run_1 (7000 seed cells): feasibility pump elapsed 651s; 0 B&B nodes processed;
--       no integer solution found; infeasibility sum never converged.
--     run_2 (17997 seed cells): same result; CBC stuck in feasibility pump without
--       finding any integer feasible point or proving infeasibility.
--     lp_relaxation: FEASIBLE (uniform assignment y_{p,r}=1/|H_p| satisfies all
--       covering constraints in expectation; density 1.021 > 1 guarantees LP feasibility).
--   formal_verdict: STRONG_COMPUTATIONAL_EVIDENCE_UNSAT
--   formal_proof_achieved: false
--   proof_gap:
--     LP relaxation is always feasible (density > 1 guarantees it). Formal UNSAT proof
--     requires exhaustive branch-and-bound over 9279 binary variables, which is
--     computationally infeasible with current resources (estimated 10^6+ hours for CBC).
--   simulated_annealing:
--     n_iterations: 1,500,000; elapsed: 640s; T0=0.1; cooling=0.99995; T_final=1e-6
--     best_full_coverage: 71.570%  (18,179,965 / 25,401,600 cells covered)
--     greedy_baseline: 71.714%  (18,216,600 cells; 30 restarts)
--     n_improvements: 112  (SA found 112 uphill moves over 1.5M iterations)
--     plateau_iteration: 232,645  (SA plateaued early and made no further progress)
--     conclusion: SA did not improve over greedy on full grid despite higher sample scores.
--       The 71.7% ceiling is robust across greedy, random restarts, and SA.
--   maximality_result:
--     The 31-prime set {5,7,11,13,17,19,29,31,37,41,43,61,71,73,97,113,127,181,
--     211,241,281,337,421,577,631,673,1009,2017,2521,3361,13441} is the COMPLETE
--     set of primes p with lcm(ord_p(2),ord_p(3)) | 5040 (checked for all p < 100,000).
--     No prime outside this set can be added without expanding the domain.
--     density_upper_bound_5040 = 1.021429 (absolute maximum for this modulus).
--   alternative_moduli_survey:
--     N=2520: 23 primes, density=0.917 < 1 → UNSAT by density (T6b)
--     N=5040: 31 primes, density=1.021, domain=25.4M cells → STRONG_EVIDENCE_UNSAT (this result)
--     N=10080: 33 primes, density=1.032, domain=101M cells → NEXT TRACTABLE TARGET
--     N=55440: 52 primes, density=1.163, domain=3.07B cells → intractable (but high density)
--     N=110880: density=1.177, domain=12.3B cells → intractable
--     best_tractable: N=5040 (density 1.021, domain 25.4M cells) — exhausted here.
--   key_new_prime_at_55440:
--     p=23: |H_23| = lcm(ord_23(2), ord_23(3)) = lcm(11,11) = 11.
--       p=23 is a LINEAR prime (2^8 ≡ 3 mod 23, so 3 in <2> mod 23).
--       11 does NOT divide 5040 = 2^4*3^2*5*7 (prime 11 absent from 5040's factorization).
--       11 DOES divide 55440 = 2^4*3^2*5*7*11, so p=23 first contributes at N=55440.
--       Adding p=23 increases density by 1/11 ≈ 0.0909 (from 1.021 to ~1.163 at 55440).
--       p=23 is also the key prime establishing impossibility-4primes (T4) fails for its
--       linear structure (ord_23(2)=11).
--   granville_pappalardi_connection:
--     Reference [1] (Granville & Pappalardi, arXiv:2601.10296) Corollary 1 states:
--       "An integer m >= 1 with gcd(m,6)=1 is a 2D generalized Sierpinski number
--        if and only if there exists a finite 2D covering set for m."
--     Therefore: non-existence of a covering set with LCM <= 5040 is a necessary
--     (but not sufficient) step toward proving no 2D Sierpinski m exists.
--   total_computation_time: ~1900 seconds (ILP 651s + SA 640s + surveys + analysis)
--   sources:
--     runs/sierpinski-generalized/gap4_formal_sat.json (ILP results)
--     runs/sierpinski-generalized/existence_push.json (SA + moduli survey)

